subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
The new species can be separated from other 

Xyphinus
species

by the reticulation of the carapace surface, which covers it entirely in both sexes (
Figs 57A, D, F
; 
59A, D, F
). The male palpal patella is provided with microsculpture (
Fig. 58C
). The female epigastric region shows a sclerotized arch and short posteriorly directed apodemes (
Figs 59H
; 
60A–E
).
